The way people think and act in different places affects how they make deals. We cannot say all people from one country act the same way. It is wrong to think "all Russians are hard to work with" or "all Japanese people are easy to work with." It is better to learn how people's ways of living affect how they make agreements.

When we meet people from other places, we often compare them to what we know from our own lives. To understand people from other places, we need to learn about their history and what they believe. Instead of trying to change their ways, we should accept them. This is very important when making deals, especially if we have less power in the talks. When we go to another country to make deals, showing respect for their ways helps everyone work better together.

Different groups have their own ways of doing things, even within the same country. Companies often have their own special ways. Some want workers to stay late at work, while others let workers go home earlier. You can see how companies are different in how workers dress, how they talk to each other, and who they choose to hire. Some companies want workers to help poor people, while others only give money to certain groups. Even in America, companies in different cities or areas can be very different.

What people think is important tells us why they act in certain ways. In some places, people think it is very important not to lose respect or cause trouble in public. These people will not say bad things about their company or their boss during talks. In other places, people think it is good to work hard for the best deal, so they may not want to agree quickly. It is good to think about these things before making deals. But it is also helpful to learn about the person you are dealing with as an individual.

The Bible says, "The person without wisdom says there is no God." This appears in Psalm 14 and starts an important discussion by two religious thinkers, Anselm and Thomas Aquinas. Both men tried to prove God exists. To compare their ideas fairly, we must accept that they speak of the God described in the Bible. While both men make good points, neither gives a complete reason to believe in God.

Let us first look at what Anselm says. He believes that understanding God comes through faith and looking inside ourselves. He says that because we can think about God in our minds, God must exist. His idea is that proof of God is found in our own thoughts. Anselm tells us we do not need to look outside ourselves to find God. Instead, we can know God exists by thinking about what we already believe to be true. This way of believing without clear proof is called faith.

Thomas Aquinas has a different view. He says we can prove God exists through careful thinking and by looking at the world around us. This would help spread Christianity because people would not need faith to believe. They could be shown God exists through clear thinking alone. Aquinas gives five ways to prove God exists. These ways look at how things change, how things are caused, why things exist, how things can be better or worse than others, and how nature works together. He shows that God must exist because the world needs God to make sense. It is like having a puzzle with one piece missing - you can know what the missing piece looks like by seeing the empty space and the pieces around it.

Writers often try to make readers feel certain ways about important things in their stories. F. Scott Fitzgerald does this well in his book The Great Gatsby. He uses special ways to help readers understand deeper meanings. One way he does this is by using colors to mean special things.

In the book, Fitzgerald makes colors like white, gray, red, and pink have special meanings. He does this carefully so readers will connect these colors with certain feelings or ideas. This is most clear with how he uses white and gray colors.

White and gray in the book often show sameness or being common. White usually means clean and rich, while gray means old or tired. We see this from the start. The two women, Daisy and Jordan, often wear white clothes. In fact, many people wear white in the story: Nick wears white pants to a party, Tom has on a white shirt when he meets his friend, and another woman puts white powder on her face.

Fitzgerald uses these colors to show ordinary things too. Nick goes to work through white city streets. The names of party guests become gray writing in his notes. A group of houses looks like pieces of white bread all the same. Simple people and places are white or gray too: the two women had a "white childhood," there are gray cars and gray land in a poor area, and even a man selling dogs is described as gray and old.

Later, Fitzgerald uses these colors to show how some things are not special anymore. When Daisy appears in white clothes and drives a white car, we start to see her differently. She becomes less special and more like everything else. This helps us understand why Gatsby's love for her might not be as wonderful as he thinks.

San Diego County grows many kinds of food because the weather is warm and sunny all year. Farmers grow tomatoes, oranges, green leaves for food, and other vegetables. They also grow fruit from trees like peaches and lemons. They make honey and grow hot peppers too.

Many people in San Diego want to buy food grown without chemicals. They often join groups that get food directly from local farms. These farms also let people visit to see how food grows. Some farms let people walk on their land to watch birds and enjoy nature.

Growing food without chemicals helps more kinds of plants and animals live on the farm. But this kind of farming costs more money. Workers must pull out bad plants by hand and find other ways to stop insects from eating the food. Small farms also cannot save money like big farms do.

The land we are talking about is near the town of Potrero in San Diego County. It is next to a big forest called Cleveland National Forest. The land is 160 acres and has many kinds of plants growing on it. It is home to many animals that need help to survive, like special rats, frogs, and birds.

Long ago, Native American people lived on this land. Later, in the late 1800s, people came to raise cows and cut wood there. Someone got this land from the government back then, and people probably used it for cows and wood since that time.

I found this land for sale and looked at ways the government could help a small farmer save money while helping wild animals. I also looked at another farm nearby that grows food without chemicals to see how it works.

Brothers share a special connection that cannot be broken. This connection includes many feelings like love, pride, anger, and sometimes being mean. Brothers know each other better than anyone else can. When they look at each other, they see themselves. When times are very hard, this connection becomes most clear, whether for good or bad. These strong feelings often come with a price. Brothers must deal with what happens because of their feelings. When they look at each other, they see who they really are, not how others see them. Their true self shows in what they do and what happens after.

In the story "The Scarlet Ibis," two brothers show these ideas. In a beautiful green place, these two boys try to do something that cannot work. One brother feels very proud but also very sad at the end, and the other brother dies. We see this through the older brother's story about Doodle, the younger brother, and how they act together. The older brother tells us his deep feelings and how he sees the world, which helps us understand why he does what he does.

The older brother does everything because of pride. From the first time he takes his little brother Doodle outside until their last walk together, he feels angry about having a weak brother. He wanted someone to play with, to run with, to climb trees with, and to swim with. But Doodle was born very sick. His heart was weak, and doctors thought he would die. He could not run or play hard games. This made the older brother very sad and angry. He even thought about hurting baby Doodle once. But when Doodle smiled at him, the older brother's anger went away. This small act gave him hope. It shows that deep down, he loved his brother, even if he didn't always show it.

The human brain is an amazing system that processes information in complex ways. Over time, as people created new things, they found new ways to describe how the brain works. First, they said it was like a flat piece of wax. Later, they said it was like paper, then like a book. Now, many people say it is like a computer. However, these simple comparisons can sometimes lead people to wrong ideas about the brain.

The brain first gets information from our senses - like touch, heat, sound, and light. These feelings become signals that the brain can understand. The brain then changes these signals in two ways. First, it builds up from small pieces of information. For example, when you see a black box on white paper, your brain first sees the color and edges. Then, your brain uses what it already knows to help you understand faster. This helps you know you are seeing a box and not a hole in the paper.

The brain also decides what information is important. For instance, when you look at grass, you see all of it but do not notice each piece. But if someone says your name in a loud room, you might hear it clearly. The brain checks what is important many times as it works with information.

The brain must store information to use it. There are three main types of storage: quick memory (for the moment), short memory (for about 20 seconds), and long memory. When information comes in, the brain changes it into a form it can keep. Words, for example, can be stored as pictures of how they look, sounds of how they speak, or ideas of what they mean. Scientists think short memory works by signals moving in circles in the brain. Long memory might be stored in special proteins.

Scientists have different ideas about how the brain organizes what it knows. One idea says the brain connects things that go together. For example, in your mind, "chair" connects to "table," and "table" connects to "wood," and so on.

In 2007, the United States faced a serious money problem. Many people lost their jobs. House prices fell sharply. Many big companies failed. These problems continue today, so we must ask: why did this happen, and how can we prevent it?

The crisis began because banks gave home loans to people who could not pay them back. The government pushed banks to do this. Two big government-supported companies, Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac, helped make these bad loans into complex financial products. When people could not pay their loans, banks lost money. This hurt the whole economy.

The problems started in 1999 when Bill Clinton was president. He wanted to win more support from voters. His government made it easier for banks to give loans. A New York Times writer, Steven Holmes, warned about this in 1999. He wrote that Fannie Mae was being pushed to give more loans to people with low and middle incomes. Holmes said this could cause problems if the economy became weak. He was right.

Several things made the problem worse. Banks created new types of home loans that were hard to understand. They also created new ways to sell these loans to others. This meant that many parts of the economy became tied to house prices. When house prices fell, it hurt everyone.

The results were very bad. In 2007, the five biggest U.S. investment banks owed $4.1 trillion in housing debts. Two of these banks were sold for very low prices. One bank failed completely. The other two had to change how they operated. Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac owed $5 trillion and had to be taken over by the government in 2008.

Let's talk about telling stories. Writers often want to share too much information at once. This can make readers stop reading or become bored.

It is better to show what happens than to just tell about it. Sometimes writers want to explain everything before getting to the interesting parts. This is not good writing. Sometimes they want to tell every small detail about every person in the story. This is also not good.

When you tell instead of show, you are just giving facts to readers. In movies, this happens when one person tells another person lots of information all at once. In books, the writer does this directly to readers.

Here is an example: Think about a story where a woman meets a man, they get married, and then he dies. If the writer only uses a few words to tell this, readers will not care about these people. But if the writer shows how the man speaks kindly to his wife, and shows how the wife's life becomes better because of him, readers will care more. They will understand why his death makes the wife sad. They will want to know what happens to her next.

Writers need to add more to their simple story ideas. Sometimes writers want to hurry and tell everything about a person right away. For example, they might want to quickly tell you that someone was in the Air Force, now works at a gas station at night, has been married two times, likes to fish, wants to own the gas station, and what he ate for breakfast. But this is not the best way to tell a story.

I watched two news programs from Columbus, Ohio. The first one was on NBC 4 on the morning of August 13, 2011. The main story was about a man in Ashley, Ohio who had hurt his wife with a knife. The man's name was Shad Hostettler. They showed his picture from the police. The story was short because it was still new. They only said he had hurt his wife many times and the police had caught him.

The second story told about a young man, Travis Buyers, who was 18 years old. Someone shot him in the Sharon Woods area, and he was badly hurt. The police had not caught anyone yet. Special police teams were looking into what happened. I felt the story was too short, maybe because the victim was a black man in a black area. I have seen that news programs often give less time to stories about people who are not white.

They then talked about a hole made by a gun in a medical flying machine. They said the shot came from a small gun. People who help solve crimes are offering money to find who did it.

Next came news about rain and storms coming on Saturday. They said it would not be too hot that weekend. They kept this story short to make people keep watching.

They also told about someone taking money from a store on Clime Road. They spent a lot of time talking about how the person who did it was black. They told how tall he was and what he was wearing.

The last story was about a man named Rene Rodriguez who sold bad things from Texas to Ohio. The court said he must stay in prison for 300 months. I thought it was strange they did not just say 25 years. They also said he was Hispanic, which did not seem important to the story.

I want to explain what an ETF is and study if it is a good way to invest money. An ETF is like a basket of different stocks that you can buy and sell easily. It works much like buying a single company's stock, but it contains many different companies.

When you buy an ETF, you get two main good things. First, your money is spread across many companies, which makes it safer. Second, you can buy or sell it quickly, just like a regular stock. Also, ETFs usually cost less money to own than other similar investment choices.

However, there are some problems. Each time you buy or sell an ETF, you must pay a small fee. But there are many different kinds of ETFs to choose from, which is good.

In this study, I looked at one ETF called IHF to see if it was really as good as owning the separate stocks it contains. To make this easier to understand, I only looked at the ten biggest companies in this ETF, which make up about 64% of its total value.

When I studied the numbers, I found something interesting. If someone bought just these ten stocks instead of the whole ETF, they might make more money - about 16% more. Also, these ten stocks together seemed less risky than the whole ETF.

To make sure these findings were real and not just by chance, I needed to look at how much each stock's price usually changes. This would help show if the difference between owning the ETF and owning just the ten stocks was important.

Looking at Figure 17, we saw a big drop in travel records during the third month. This was disappointing, and we were not sure why it happened. When winter comes to our school in the Northeast, fewer people ride bikes or walk to work. This might explain some of the drop. December is also when the fall school term ends, and everyone is busy with final work and grades. Many people might have forgotten to write down how they traveled. December also brings busy holiday time, and students and teachers leave for a month. Many do not need to come to school at all. School starts again in late January, which might explain why few people wrote records that month. But this does not explain why February had such low numbers.

Projects like this often start with great interest that then falls. To fight this drop, we made a special week in March called "Ride Together Week." This helped get more travel records that month. One of our big problems was keeping people interested when they naturally lose interest, and when school breaks happen.

Another problem is that people like driving their own cars. They like being free to go where they want, when they want. This is part of how we live. So we needed to give people good reasons to try other ways to travel. We gave many small prizes like food cards for eating places, coffee shops, and stores in town. It would have been good to see what bigger prizes might have done - like giving away a good bike or a special car that uses less gas. This might have helped keep people interested. Our prizes stayed the same all through the project. If we had made the prizes better as time went on, more people might have stayed with us. The gift cards worked well at first, but if we had said in December we would give away bikes, and then in January said we would give away a special car, more people might have kept writing their travel records.

I studied fifteen early films made by Thomas Edison between 1895 and 1901. These were special films that used clever methods to create magic-like effects. Most of these films followed similar rules in how they were made. They were filmed inside, used simple camera positions, and were very short.

The camera always stayed in one place, like watching a stage play. This way of filming came from theater shows, where people sit and watch from their seats. In these films, actors usually moved from left to right across the screen. They did not walk toward or away from the camera. For example, in a film called "Uncle Josh in a Spooky Hotel" (1900), all the action happens from side to side.

These films were always shot from far away or middle distance. The camera never showed close pictures of faces or things. This was like watching a theater show, where you see everything happening on the whole stage at once. The actors stayed at about the same distance from the camera throughout the film.

Most of these early films were very short, usually less than one minute long. They showed simple tricks like making people or things appear and disappear. They did not tell long stories. While viewers saw what looked like one continuous scene, the filmmakers actually stopped the camera and started again to create the special effects. A good example is "The Execution of Mary, Queen of Scots" (1895). If you watch carefully, you can see where they stopped filming to create the effect of the execution.

The old style of writing called "Gothic" combines both old and new ideas. Some people liked it, while others said it had no value. The first Gothic book, "The Castle of Otranto" by Horace Walpole, mixed old stories with new ways of writing to create something different.

Gothic writing uses many ideas from the Middle Ages, including old buildings and customs. When "The Castle of Otranto" was written, the word "gothic" was used to describe many different things from the past. Many people thought these old ways were not as good as new ones.

What made Gothic writing special was how it mixed old theater-like stories with the new way of writing books. This let readers better understand how characters thought and felt. This is why Gothic stories are still interesting to readers today, even though they are very old.

One important idea in Gothic books is the code of good behavior called "chivalry." This came from the Middle Ages, when knights had to follow special rules about being brave and honest. Writers like Walpole used these old ideas because they thought their own time needed more of these good qualities.

When Walpole wrote his book, his country had many problems. He may have thought people in his time were not as good or honest as people in the past. We can see this in his story through characters like Frederic, who shows many of the good qualities of an old-time knight. The way Walpole writes about these characters sometimes makes them seem bigger than life, which became a common way of writing Gothic stories.

Moving goods from start to finish is called supply chain management. This process begins when a customer orders something and ends when they receive it. Keith Oliver, who helped businesses work better, first used this term in 1982. He explained how to plan and control the movement of goods to make customers happy quickly and well.

There are six main parts to moving goods: making things, getting materials, keeping products ready, choosing where to put things, moving items around, and sharing information. Business leaders use these six parts to serve customers well.

Making things is the first and most important part. Leaders must know what to make and how many items to produce. They look at what people want to buy to make these choices. They also need to pick the best places to make things, thinking about how much they can make and how good the products will be.

After choosing where to make things, leaders must plan when workers will do their jobs and how to keep machines working well. Every small part of making things must be carefully planned. If not, it can waste time and money. For example, stores like Wal-Mart and Target have clear plans for everything - from how workers should dress to how trucks should bring in goods. These plans help everything work smoothly.

The next important part is getting materials. Leaders must decide what each factory does best and when to ask other companies for help. Sometimes, different places make different parts of one product. Leaders might ask other companies to help make things if it saves money or helps make better products faster.

Books from the time of Queen Victoria often describe small details and focus on rich people's lives. However, two famous books from this time, "Oliver Twist" and "Wuthering Heights," are different. These stories use mystery and strange events to help readers better understand the characters' feelings and reasons for their actions.

In "Oliver Twist," we often see these strange events through dreams or dream-like moments. For example, when Oliver is shot, he experiences the event again in his mind while trying to find help. In this part of the story, Oliver hears the voices of Sikes and Crackit, even though they are not really there. He sees lights and hears guns and shouting. Someone helps him move away, but he does not know who it is. Through all of this, he feels pain that will not go away.

This dream-like moment shows us how little control Oliver has over his life. He cannot do anything to help himself, even when he is in danger. It seems that the bad people in his life, like Fagin, have made Oliver feel hopeless. The way time passes also feels strange to Oliver - the days seem to disappear quickly, while the nights feel both very long and very short.

Two years ago, I helped young students after school with their studies. While I could help with many subjects, I was best at teaching reading and writing. A teacher asked me to help a young boy named Adrian. He was about nine years old and had trouble reading.

I noticed something strange about Adrian's reading. He knew some letters well but struggled with others. He spoke English perfectly, and I knew he came from a Spanish-speaking family. One day, when most students were away on a trip, I met Adrian's mother. She only spoke Spanish. Even with my basic Spanish, I could talk with her a little. Then I understood: Adrian could read, but he did not know English letters well.

I share this story to show how language problems affect our schools, especially in California. Sometimes these problems are hard to see. Even when children speak English well, reading can be very hard for them. We know this is a problem, so what should we do? For Adrian, the answer was simple: he needed help learning English letters and their sounds. But for children who do not speak much English, we need more than one solution. We have many ways to help: teaching in two languages, using only English, having special teachers, or giving extra English classes. No single way will solve everything. We need to use all of these ways together.

Teaching in two languages is very good for all students, not just those who speak Spanish first. Studies show that children who learn in two languages do better in school than others. Some people worry this wastes money and only helps a few students. This is not true. If we teach all children this way, everyone gains. We do not need every teacher to speak two languages. Instead, we can have special helpers who speak both languages work with the students.

From when we are young, most of us learn about something greater than ourselves. Some go to religious schools, while others search for answers in different ways. Many accept the religious beliefs their parents teach them. Others say there is nothing beyond what they can see and know. People may follow one set of beliefs, then change to another later. Whatever we choose, we all try to understand life's big questions in our own way. We look for understanding, like searching for light in the dark.

"A red bird," my father said when I asked about his favorite bird. We sat on our front steps, listening to rain hit the metal roof as we smoked. Water ran down the sides, making the plants very wet. He looked into the rain, seeming both thoughtful and far away. He had become much thinner, and his clothes were loose on him. His hair was thinner than before, too. As he kept looking at the rain, not meeting my eyes, I felt very alone. I was afraid and could not tell him how much I would miss him. Speaking about it would make it too real for both of us. I moved closer to him, and we both watched the rain fall in the evening light.

My father died in December that year, just after I turned twenty-two. The medical treatments did not stop his pain, but kept him alive longer than doctors said he would live. I could not understand why he had to suffer more. I questioned why this happened. At night, alone, I stopped praying. I thought if there was a God, He no longer heard me.

I did not want to see my father die, so I stayed away. I could not watch the person who gave me life leave this world. I wanted to remember him as he lived, not as he died. I knew my father better than anyone, and I knew he would not want his only child to watch him die. I stayed in bed for three days, waiting to hear news.

No one called to tell me when he died.

John Taylor was an early supporter of the Republican way of thinking in America. He worked mainly as a farmer, and this work, along with his short time in government, made him known for speaking strongly about personal freedom and government power. His love of farming shaped most of his ideas about how government should work. He tried to protect and support farming because he thought it was the best kind of work.

Taylor believed the United States had a special chance to make a perfect system. This was because the new country had no old rules to hold it back, which let people create a government where they could rule themselves. He strongly believed in the natural rights that all people have. He thought these rights were all connected - if you lose one right, you lose them all. He said the government should never be able to take away these rights. Some people talked about how, in nature, strong and clever but bad people got ahead. Taylor said this must not happen in a proper society.

To make this better society, Taylor thought we needed a government that understood both the good and bad in people. He believed very strongly that things were either right or wrong. He said that since people run governments, governments show both good and bad human qualities. He thought good rules were ones that protected what people owned, helped farming grow, and stopped big business from getting too powerful. He believed people always act for their own good, but this only becomes bad when people hurt others to help themselves. We need good government to control people's bad side, but we must watch the government carefully.

Taylor, like other Republicans of his time, wanted people to follow the Constitution exactly as it was written. He wanted a small federal government that could only do what the Constitution clearly said it could do. He knew that a big federal government would cost too much money and might become too powerful. But he also thought that just reading the Constitution's words simply, without thinking about what the writers meant, could cause problems. He thought the Declaration of Independence was even more important than the Constitution because it clearly showed that the United States was made up of separate states working together, not just one big nation.

I looked down at the toilet, my mind empty as I saw what was there. I watched without feeling, like someone who sees but does not want to understand. Thoughts came and went quickly. My mind worked so well that it felt like I wasn't really thinking at all.

Once, an artist told me to buy a book called "The New Drawing on the Right Side of the Brain." Since I was six, I wanted to learn to draw. The book teaches everything about drawing, from how to hold a pencil to how our brain sees lines. One lesson tells us to put a frame around what we want to draw. This makes a complex picture, like a fruit bowl in a kitchen, become simple.

At that moment, looking at the toilet, I could not imagine such a frame. I could only stand and stare. Famous artists had their special colors - Picasso used blue, Monet liked green. If I were to call myself an artist, this would be my brown period.

My fingers touched the toilet handle, my hand moving through the air as if making art. The water moved smoothly and clearly. Small pieces broke away and disappeared. Moving more quickly the second time, I pushed the handle again. The brown mess stayed at the bottom of the toilet, not moving.

I stood there in my work clothes, green tie around my neck, holding a mop. I looked at what someone had left for the cleaning workers at Rite Aid. After trying to flush several more times, I reached for the toilet paper. I wrapped my hand many times until it was covered like a thick glove. Then, I bent down and reached into the bowl, like reaching into an oven for food...

Young people are dying while driving cars. Several things work together to make driving very dangerous for the youngest drivers in America. Health experts say one part of the problem is that young minds are not ready for the dangers of driving. Not having enough experience is another big problem. This lack of experience leads to more deadly crashes, cars turning over, driving too fast, and cars going off the road.

Young drivers have more problems when they drive with friends their age - which they often do. A study in Southern California showed that more crashes happen when young passengers are in the car.

California and other states have tried to make young drivers safer. They give special licenses that only let young people drive at certain times and do not allow other young people to ride with them.

But these special licenses are only a short-term answer. The real problem is that the youngest drivers, as a group, cannot handle the dangers and duties of driving well enough. One expert who studies how people think believes that even age eighteen is too young to drive. He found that people under age twenty often take risks just for fun. It makes sense to wait until people are older to let them drive.

If we keep giving driver's licenses to young people, more deadly crashes will happen. In the coming years, many more young people will be old enough to drive, which could lead to more deaths.

The answer could be simple. Schools could still teach driving, but no one under eighteen could drive a car. New drivers would still need to learn and practice with an adult for many hours before getting a full license. Because young drivers have problems in all states, one law for the whole country would be a good way to keep young people safe.

This idea is not new, but it could save many lives.

This paper looks at a brain condition that affects how people process sound. The condition is called Central Auditory Processing Disorder, or CAPD for short.

First, I will explain what CAPD is. People with CAPD can hear sounds normally, but their brains cannot process these sounds correctly. For example, they may have trouble understanding words when there is noise in the room. Their ears work fine, but their brains have difficulty making sense of what they hear.

The study of CAPD began in the 1950s. At that time, doctors called it by a different name. They were trying to help children who had trouble with speaking and understanding others. In 1977, many doctors met to share what they knew about CAPD and to plan new studies.

People with CAPD may have several problems. They might not know where sounds are coming from. They may find it hard to tell different sounds apart. Some cannot understand when someone is joking by the way they speak. Others might have trouble remembering the order of sounds they hear.

To find out if someone has CAPD, doctors watch how the person responds to different sounds. They may ask the person to complete special listening tests. The person might need to pick out specific words or numbers when hearing many sounds at once. There is no single test that can show for sure if someone has CAPD. Doctors also do not know what causes this condition.

I want to work in social services to help children who have been hurt by their families. I also want to help families who are having problems. I believe I can bring important things to this work: helping others, showing respect, doing what is right, and always learning to do my job better. These values are not just important for the job - they are important to who I am.

I always knew I wanted to help people, but I was not sure how. During my school years, I saw many people run away from their problems. Some people tried to solve their problems in ways that were not good. This led me to study how people think and act in college. After finishing school in 2009, I took some time to think about what to do next.

That summer, I met a young person who was trying to get away from parents who were hurting him. When he called the police, I went to help. I talked to the police and told them about my education. They asked me to speak with the parents. The parents tried to say their son was causing trouble and making things up. After this, I knew I wanted to work helping children with family problems.

I also believe everyone should be treated fairly. Our society says each person is special, yet many people try to be like everyone else. I choose to be different. In school, I showed this by the way I looked and dressed. I joined groups that helped people who were different. I spoke up when I saw people being treated badly because of who they were. I will keep working to make sure everyone is treated fairly.

This paper looks at two ways to understand sleep problems, especially when people cannot sleep well. One way looks at how our bodies work and what we get from our parents. The other way looks at how where we live, our culture, and our money affect our sleep.

When people have trouble sleeping, doctors put these problems into different groups. The main groups are problems with falling asleep or staying asleep, and problems with strange things happening during sleep. Some sleep problems happen because of other health issues or because of drugs people take.

Not being able to sleep well is a common problem. It can mean having trouble falling asleep or staying asleep for a month or more. Some people have the opposite problem - they sleep too much. Others might fall asleep suddenly during the day. There are also people who walk or have bad dreams while sleeping.

Scientists have found that special cells in the brain control when we sleep and when we are awake. They did tests with mice to learn about these cells. They found that certain parts of brain cells help control sleep. When these parts work correctly, they help us sleep normally. If these parts do not work well, people might need medicine to help them sleep.

If someone gets these sleep problems from their parents, it can make life hard. It can cause trouble at school or work, especially when they need to focus on boring tasks. This shows how sleep problems can affect many parts of a person's life.

I have been a student at University Park for more than two years. Moving around our large school area is often hard for many students, including me. When I first came here, I lived in East Halls, which is very far from the center of school. Walking from my room in Stuart Hall to my classes in Willard building could take 25 minutes, especially when the weather was bad. 

An older student told me that not long ago, East Halls stood alone, far from other buildings. Now that empty land has new sports fields and big buildings, including places for food and health care. As our school grows bigger, it gets harder to move from place to place. The best answer to this problem is the bicycle. But just having bikes is not enough. Students must use them, and the school must make it easy for people to ride bikes.

A friend who just started riding bikes again told me something interesting. He said he did not know why he ever stopped riding. He thinks bikes are the best way to move around school. Riding a bike is good for your health and uses very little energy. A simple meal can give you enough power to ride 30 miles or more.

I now live away from school, but my home is as far from classes as some school rooms are. Buying a bike was very smart. Every day, I need to go to Thomas building, which takes 25 minutes to walk to from my home. On my bike, I can get there in 5 minutes if I ride fast. The only problem is that Pollock Road, the fastest way there, can be hard to travel on.

Walking is fine, but I do not have enough time. Without my bike, I would have to walk everywhere. Walking to Thomas building every day would take 40 more minutes of my time. That means more than two hours every week just for one class. When you think about all my other classes and things I need to do, that is too much time to spend walking.

In his book "Brave New World," writer Aldous Huxley shows us problems with technology and money-driven societies. He creates a future world where people think the group is more important than any single person. From birth, people are taught to seek quick happiness above everything else.

The people in this world are controlled by leaders who tell them what to think. When we look at the book through the ideas of Karl Marx, we can see Huxley was worried about how society was changing. Marx's ideas about how groups of people become the same and lose their special qualities help us understand the book's message about problems in the growing money system of Huxley's time.

The book shows how people are kept from knowing the truth about their place in society. The common people only care about getting things for themselves. This happens because the leaders control what people think. In the book, the lower groups of people, called Delta and Gamma, cannot think for themselves. While they sleep, they hear messages that make them want to buy things and enjoy themselves without thinking deeply.

The higher groups, called Alpha and Beta, know more about how things work, but most do not try to change anything. Only a few people, like the character Bernard, question the way things are.

In this future world, real friendships between different kinds of people do not exist. Even the main characters in the book seem flat and simple. This might be Huxley's way of saying that technology and money-focused societies take away people's ability to be themselves. There is no real love in this world. Men only talk about how women look, and women speak without shame about their physical relationships.

Each group of people accepts their place in society without question. They follow orders and keep buying things, thinking this makes them better. This is exactly what Marx warned about - people being fooled into thinking they are happy while being controlled by others.

I took a class about Islam at my school four years ago. In class, we often talked about whether Islam was a religion that wanted peace or not. This question is even more important now. Since the attacks of September 11, I have watched how news groups changed their views. At first, they were against Islam. Now, they show much more acceptance of Islam in America. In 2001, no one would have thought we could have someone like Barack Obama, who has family ties to Islam, run for president.

The life story of Muhammad interests me because what I read seems different from what I knew before. I had learned that Muhammad made people join his religion by force. I thought he took control of other groups and made them become Muslim. But the book shows him as a good man who was not understood by others. It says people came to him because they saw the truth in his words.

The book tells stories about Muhammad that are very much like stories about Jesus. For example, it says Muhammad took a small amount of food and made it bigger to feed forty men. I think the writers wanted to show Muhammad as a quiet, truthful man who did special things. This bothers me because it makes Jesus' life and special works seem less important. It feels like they are taking Jesus' story and using it for Muhammad.

The book has many stories about people becoming Muslim on their own. But these stories often come from someone who heard it from someone else, who heard it from another person. This makes me doubt if the stories are true.

What troubles me most is how the book shows Muhammad as a good, quiet, and wise man. But what we know from the past shows he was not always gentle and quiet. I wonder if Muslims today know the real story of how Muhammad gained his power.

The ideas Jesus taught during his life were quickly changed as Christian thinking grew after his death. Looking at history, we can see Christianity moving further from what Jesus first taught. Today, more people seem to understand this and want change. While some people want to keep old ways of thinking, they may be too few to stop change.

In the coming years, Christians will learn more about their history. They will want to know what Jesus really meant to teach, separate from ideas added later. This may take many years, but change will come. Christian thinking will move back toward its first form. People will remove added teachings one by one, like turning back time. In the end, only Jesus' original message from God will remain.

When this happens in America and Europe, many people will try to follow only what Jesus taught. Churches will still be important, but they will lead people back to simpler beliefs. Instead of many different ways of thinking about Christianity, more people will share the same ideas. Groups that were different will become more alike.

History shows us big changes can happen. The Romans once killed Christians, but later became Christian themselves. America once had slaves, but now has African-American leaders. Christianity will also change, going back to find its true beginning. To do this, people will need to understand that Jesus often spoke in word pictures, not just plain facts.

Let's look at how this all started. Before Christianity, there was only Judaism. By the time Rome took control of Jerusalem in 63 BCE, Jewish people believed in one God, followed their holy books, and thought God had given them their religion. But Jewish people were not all the same. They split into different groups: the Sadducees, Pharisees, Essenes, Zealots, and regular people who were the largest group.

I think "The Jungle" shows that people are naturally wanting things only for themselves. They care about making their own lives better but do not help others who have less. The book shows this in several ways, especially through the factory owners and managers.

These business leaders only want to make their companies bigger and richer. They do not care who gets hurt as they try to grow their business. In the book, Upton Sinclair describes how the factory buildings stand dark against the sky, with smoke coming from big chimneys. This smoke spreads far into the distance. He wants us to see how the factories hurt the air and land around them. The owners do not worry about how this affects people or animals. They ignore the bad smoke from their factories and the animal waste that runs from the many animal holding areas.

The owners and managers also treat their workers badly. They only care about money, not people. Workers must work long hours in dangerous places. The owners can tell many workers to leave their jobs without warning. At that time, there were no laws to protect workers. Managers could make people work faster and faster in unsafe places.

The book shows how the workers, mostly poor people from other countries, had to accept these terrible conditions. They had no help from the government. While there were worker groups called unions, these often took advantage of the workers too. The workers were so badly treated that the book compares them to slaves. They were always close to having no food and depended completely on the cruel factory owners, just like slaves depended on their masters.

Edgar Allan Poe wrote a poem called "Dream-Land" which he thought was one of his best works. In this poem, he uses the word "Thule" two times. This word comes from old stories about a far-away place north of Britain. People long ago thought this was the edge of the world they knew.

While this idea came from old writers, Poe likely got it from somewhere else. He read many German writers, and one of them, named Goethe, wrote about Thule too. Goethe was a famous writer who wrote a long work called "Faust." Inside this work was a shorter poem about "The King of Thule."

Goethe's poem tells about a sad king whose wife died. She gave him a special cup before she died. After she was gone, the king drank a lot and cried when he thought about her. He gave everything he owned to his children, except the cup. Then he went to a high place above the sea, threw the cup into the water, and died.

Poe's "Dream-Land" seems very much like Goethe's story. Both tell about dark, lonely places and sad memories. Poe wrote about Thule in two different works: "Dream-Land" and another story called "The Pit and the Pendulum."

The two poems feel like they go together. In "Dream-Land," the writer talks about a dark place where he sees dead friends and a world without bright colors. This is very much like the sad king in Goethe's poem, who lost his wife and did not want to live anymore.

Poe knew about Goethe's writing. He would have read it because many people were making new versions of Goethe's work at that time. Also, other writers Poe liked, such as Tennyson, respected Goethe's work very much.

Let me explain a legal case about safety in a store in California.

A woman named Jennifer Palmer fell in a store and hurt her back. She fell because there was spilled food on the floor that had not been cleaned up. Before she fell, two workers told the store manager about the spill. The manager, Paul Martin, did not clean it up because he was eating his dinner. The spill stayed on the floor for thirty minutes before Palmer fell.

The store, called D&D Markets, had five other people fall and get hurt in that same year. Palmer wants the store to pay her money for her injury. She also wants extra money to punish the store for being careless.

Under California law, a person can get extra money if they can show the other person acted very badly. The law says the bad actions must show the person knew they could hurt someone but did not care.

Palmer can probably win her case for extra money because:
1. The manager knew about the spill
2. He was told twice about it
3. He did nothing to clean it up
4. Many people had fallen in his store before
5. He chose to eat instead of keeping customers safe

The law wants store managers to keep people safe. When they know about something dangerous but do nothing, they can be made to pay extra money as punishment.

She felt empty inside, wanting something she could not name. This feeling began when she was fourteen and stayed with her at seventeen. She knew she wanted to be close to someone, but no boys interested her. Several boys liked her and tried to get her attention, but she felt nothing for them. She often wondered why she was different from other girls her age. After thinking about it for years, she still had no answer. She continued to live her life while wondering about these feelings.

Life at home was usually quiet. Her parents were peaceful people who rarely fought. They only disagreed when their daughter wanted more freedom. While her parents were calm, she was full of life and fun. People liked her because she was both friendly and kind.

But this day was not peaceful. As she walked through the house looking for something to do, she heard her mother cry out from the kitchen. She ran to find her mother on the floor.

"Mom! What happened?" she called out.

Her mother was breathing hard and saying "ow" over and over. 

"Please take me to the hospital," her mother said with difficulty.

"Show me where to hold you," the daughter said. She was glad she had learned how to lift heavy things. She carried her mother to the car, placed her carefully in the back seat, and drove to the hospital.

The hospital had strong smells, but she did not notice them. She was thinking only about her mother. She carried her mother inside and called for help. Medical workers came quickly with a bed on wheels. They took her mother away for care, leaving the daughter to wait and worry.

Later, she learned her mother had fallen while trying to reach a flower vase on the highest shelf.

This study looked at how eating a Mediterranean-style diet affects heart health. The Mediterranean diet includes lots of plant foods, fish, and healthy fats from plants. It has fewer animal products and unhealthy fats. A small amount of wine is allowed.

Earlier studies showed that people who follow this diet have better heart health and live longer. One study found that this diet works better than a low-fat diet for losing weight and improving blood tests in overweight people.

The study watched 74,886 women between ages 38 and 63 for twenty years. These women were nurses working in eleven different states. None had heart problems or diabetes when the study began. Every few years, the women filled out forms about what they ate. Most women stayed in the study for all twenty years.

The researchers carefully checked hospital records and death reports to confirm heart problems and strokes. They also looked at other things that affect health, like exercise, smoking, and weight.

To get better results, they averaged each woman's eating habits over time. They also considered other things that might affect the results, such as age and exercise.

The study found that women who followed the Mediterranean diet most closely had fewer heart problems and strokes. During the twenty years, 2,391 women had heart problems, 1,763 had strokes, and 1,077 died from heart disease or stroke. Women who followed the diet best had about 30 percent fewer heart problems than those who followed it least.

A young actress stands on a street with a sign. The sign suggests that the spirit of Hitler lives in Burma, a country in Southeast Asia.

Since 1962, Burma has been controlled by military leaders who took power by force. In 2007, many people went into the streets to protest against the government. Buddhist religious leaders wearing orange clothes led these protests. This became known as the "Saffron Movement" because of the color of their clothes.

At first, the government let the protests continue peacefully. But then, things became violent. The military attacked religious buildings and hurt many people. They stopped news reporters from other countries from taking pictures or writing stories. They killed one news photographer from Japan just because he was watching the protests. The government said only thirteen people died. But one military leader who left his job said thousands of people were killed.

This kind of violent control has happened many times in history. Leaders often try to stop people who disagree with them. In ancient Rome, rulers said the gods chose them to lead. In Japan, people once believed their rulers were gods.

One famous example happened in China in 1989. Many students and workers gathered in Tiananmen Square to protest against their government. The Chinese government says about 200 to 300 people died, but the Chinese Red Cross says between 2,000 and 3,000 people were killed. Another terrible event was in Rwanda in the 1990s, where one group of people tried to kill another group. And of course, there was Hitler's time in power, when many Jewish people were killed.

Duke Ellington was one of the greatest jazz musicians in history. He led his band for many years and was very good at writing music that showed how well each player could perform. While he played piano, his most important work was as a writer of music. He knew how to create pieces that let musicians play freely while also writing parts that needed to be played exactly as written. He understood how each player sounded and how to make them sound good together.

One of his famous pieces is called "Creole Love Call." In this piece, he used a singer's voice like another instrument in the band, without using words. This was something new at the time. The piece has six main parts:

Part 1: The voice and wind instruments play back and forth
Part 2: A trumpet plays the main tune
Part 3: A high clarinet plays while the piano adds soft notes
Part 4: The whole band plays together
Part 5: The wind instruments play high notes while others keep time
Part 6: The voice and winds play together again, with the voice making special sounds

The piece ends with the voice running up and down and one final note from a trombone.

Ellington wrote other pieces that used voices in new ways. In "Hot and Bothered," he had a trumpet player and a singer make sounds that worked together well. In "It Don't Mean a Thing," he used a special way of playing the trombone to start the song. These pieces show how Ellington was very good at mixing different sounds to make interesting music.

How do living things change over time? What limits the way they can change? In 1917, a scientist named D'Arcy Thompson said that we could not yet describe living things using numbers and math. This is still true today.

Recently, scientists have used math to study how sea animal shells grow and change over time. Our study looks at a type of sea animal called Prunum. We want to understand how these shells grow and change from parent to child, and over many years.

We took X-ray pictures of different Prunum shells to measure their shapes. We put these numbers into a computer program called CerioShell. This helped us see what kinds of shell shapes are possible for Prunum. We also watched how the animals grow to better understand how they change over long periods.

A shell is like a tube that goes around in circles. These circles are called whorls. The whorls turn around a center line called the columella. The whorls can grow at different speeds. A line between each whorl is called a suture. The biggest whorl is usually the last one, called the body whorl. All other whorls make up the spire. The top of the spire is called the apex, and the bottom is called the base. The animal comes out through a hole called the aperture.

You can look at shells from different sides: the top, bottom, front (where you can see the aperture), and back. Usually, people look at shells from the front, with the top pointing up.

To count whorls, look at the shell from the top. Find where the first line between whorls starts. Draw a line to split the shell in two parts. Count the whorls from this line. You can count parts of whorls in quarters.

As the animal builds its shell, it makes a series of openings that follow a path. Scientists can measure this path by looking at the center of each opening and how wide and tall it is.

We can draw this path and write it as math numbers. Once we have these numbers, we can change them to see how different shells might grow.

In Indonesia, the number of babies and young children who die has stayed about the same for the past ten years. The country has made progress in some areas, like providing clean water. However, it has not made enough progress in keeping mothers and children healthy.

More births now happen with trained health workers present - about 72 out of 100 births. But many of these workers are traditional helpers who cannot deal with serious problems during birth. This means many mothers still die from losing too much blood. Also, fewer sick children under five years old are seeing doctors for stomach problems. Not enough mothers get care after giving birth.

Special operations to help mothers give birth safely happen less often than they should. Only 4 out of 100 births use this method. In cities, 7 out of 100 births use this method, but in rural areas, only 2 out of 100 do. This shows that health care is better in cities than in rural areas. Also, rich people get much more health care than poor people. Poor people often cannot pay for care they need.

Indonesia must decide how to fix these problems. They could make special programs just for mothers and babies, or they could make the whole health system better. Special programs can show quick results and are easier to manage. But these programs can cause problems. When lots of money goes to one health problem, other health needs get less attention. Also, having many different programs doing the same work wastes time and money. Workers must fill out too many forms, and programs often do not work well together.

Over the past hundred years, popular music has grown to include many different kinds. Today, there are so many kinds of music that it is hard to list them all. Each kind of music, like rap, rock, country, jazz, and folk, has created smaller groups within itself.

Heavy Metal rock music has become one of the most interesting kinds of popular music in the past forty years. It shows many different feelings, usually dark ones. Soon after Heavy Metal began, people found they could change it in many ways. They made new kinds of Heavy Metal, and then made even more kinds from those. This continues today.

Now there are so many different kinds of Heavy Metal that it is hard to say exactly what it is. It has taken ideas from many other kinds of music. To understand Heavy Metal today, we need to understand how it grew into more than just one kind of music.

Heavy Metal is often about dark things. It uses more of everything - more loud sounds, more angry words, and more show on stage. The people who play Heavy Metal must be very good at playing their instruments. In the middle of the 1970s, many musicians used drugs, which led them to make strange music. Heavy Metal was different from other popular music because it showed dark feelings that most other music did not show. Some of these dark ideas came from music written hundreds of years ago.

One of the first Heavy Metal songs might have been "Helter Skelter" by the Beatles. They wrote this song to show they could make music as strong as the Rolling Stones. The song had dark words and showed the effects of drugs. They put this song on their White Album.

Many years before artists began making strange dream-like pictures, Henri Rousseau was already painting his own dreams. His famous work "The Dream" from 1910 shows a woman looking with wonder at the land she sees in her sleep. The painting also shows what Rousseau himself wanted most - to be accepted and praised by other artists. He faced a hard choice in trying to reach this goal.

"The Dream" shows the battle inside Rousseau: should he paint like others to be accepted, or should he follow his own special way of making art?

To understand this better, we should know about Rousseau's life. He was born in 1844 in Laval, France. His father fixed metal things and sold hardware, and had enough money to live well. Rousseau never went to art school. Until he was forty, he worked for the city collecting money from people at road stations. His life was very sad at times - his first wife died, and he lost eight babies, leaving him with just one daughter named Julia. To feel better, he turned to painting.

Unlike other artists of his time who painted fancy pictures of poor people, Rousseau painted more simply, like ordinary people did. He wanted very much to be accepted by other artists. This wish makes sense because he started painting when he was older and never had proper training. He was making art at the same time as many famous painters.

Rousseau did not get much attention for his work until Henri Matisse was becoming well-known. A writer named Jan Gordon said these two artists were very different: Matisse tried hard not to paint in common ways, while Rousseau just wanted to paint pictures that would help him fit in with other artists.

Many wise people have seen a close link between what is right and what is beautiful. I believe there is a basic reason for this connection. The poet John Keats wrote that beauty and truth are the same thing, and this is all we need to know.

We learn most things in life through school or personal experience. But we seem to understand right and wrong, and beauty, in a different way. When we study these things, we try to explain why something is beautiful or why an action is right, rather than making rules about them.

When we talk about art or right actions, we can never fully explain why they are good. For example, when people discuss the famous painting Mona Lisa, they might talk about its colors or its place in history. But these words do not fully tell us why it is great art. Often, when someone talks about their favorite art, they first say, "There is just something about it." I think both art and right actions have qualities that cannot be fully described.

The writer Flannery O'Connor said that we tell stories because simple statements are not enough. No matter how well we describe a story, there is always something more that we cannot explain. I believe the same is true about right and wrong.

I think right actions and art are closely connected because we feel them deeply in a way that goes beyond words. This connection is especially strong in stories and books. Unlike music or painting, writing deals directly with human actions and choices. Stories are important to us because they show us what matters in life, just as our own lives teach us what is right and important.

Today's Germany is a strong and united nation. Its culture spreads from the mountains in Munich to the northern city of Kiel on the sea. You can feel this same culture from Cologne on the Rhine River, through the middle of the country, to Dresden on the Elbe River. Germany's culture comes from many different groups of people who lived there long ago.

The old land of the German people was called Germania. No one knows for sure how it got this name. A writer named Tacitus said the name came from a group called the Tungrians. They were known as Germans before they moved across the Rhine River to fight the Gauls. Julius Caesar was the first to write the word "Germanus" when he wrote about his wars with the Gauls. He got this word from the Gauls to tell the difference between the people he had won battles against and those he had not. Some think the name means "neighbor" in the old Gaul language. Others say it comes from their fighting stick called a "ger," or from old words that meant "to shout."

Tacitus wrote in the year 98 that the Germans were the first people in their land. He thought they did not mix with other groups. He asked why anyone would leave warm lands to come to Germania with its cold weather and dark forests, unless it was already their home.

The Romans did not want to live in Germania. They went there to get goods and sometimes to fight, but they usually went back to Rome. The German groups began to appear about two thousand years ago. They lived near the edge of the Roman Empire, where they traded goods. Many Germans also worked as soldiers in the Roman army.

The play Twelfth Night shows us that hiding who you are can help for a while, but people must eventually show their true selves. If they do not, they might lose their real identity. However, when people stop hiding, they might lose friends. So, people must choose between staying true to themselves or keeping their relationships with others. Some people might not mind finding out they were fooled, but others will be angry about it.

When someone pretends to be the opposite sex, it raises important questions. The main question is why they feel they must hide who they are. In the play, Viola does this to stay safe. She says she needs help to serve a noble man, and changing her clothes helps protect her.

Viola, who is new to this strange land, thinks she must act like a man to stay safe from bad people. This works, but it keeps her from making friends with other women. Things get harder when Olivia thinks Viola is really a man named Sebastian and falls in love with her. Also, Viola must hide her own loving feelings for Orsino, who tells her that no woman could love him as much as she does.

Today's readers might see this story differently. The play shows how hiding one's true self can help bring hidden feelings into the open, especially for Olivia and Orsino. We might wonder if Olivia likes Cesario because she thinks Cesario is a man, or if she might have hidden feelings for women. But this is probably not what the writer meant. Shakespeare seems to be making fun of people who only care about how others look.

We can see this when Olivia quickly changes her love from Cesario to Sebastian, and then starts to think of Viola as family instead of someone to love, calling her "sister."

The German control of its colonies was often very harsh. This was especially true in South West Africa, where they killed many local Herero and Nama people. However, how Germany ruled its colonies was different in each place. The same was true for schools in these colonies.

When the British took control of German East Africa in 1919, they found many African people who could read and write. Other German colonies like Kamerun also had good schools. But South West Africa (now called Namibia) was very different.

In East Africa, the government built schools and helped teach local people. But in South West Africa, they left teaching African people mostly to church groups, giving them little help. The government did spend much money on schools for European children there. They built public schools and helped church schools that taught European children. These choices about schools affected South West Africa for many years. While other German colonies had many educated African people, most people in South West Africa could not read or write.

Many things made South West Africa different. This study looks at these reasons, especially how the European settlers and government officials thought about African people.

Many people have written about schools in German colonies. Most early writing was in German, from the time when Germany had colonies. These early writers mostly told about how the schools worked. Later, English writers compared schools in different German colonies. They showed how each colony was different. One important writer, Cohen, studied why schools in South West Africa and East Africa were so different. He found that having many European settlers in South West Africa changed how schools worked there.

South West Africa had better weather than other German colonies, though much of it was dry desert land. Because of this better weather, more Europeans lived there. By 1913, almost 15,000 European people lived in South West Africa. The next highest number was in East Africa, with only 5,336 European settlers.

The United States and Mexico were not friendly nations for many years, from 1836 to 1893. The worst time in their relationship was during the Mexican-American War of 1846-1848. In this war, the United States fought Mexico and won. As a result, the United States took control of Texas and land in the Southwest.

The two countries had many differences that caused problems. They did not share the same religion, culture, or ways of life. This is common when two countries share a border. For example, Mexico and Cuba have had long-running problems with the United States, while other countries in Latin America have better relationships.

Religion was a big reason for the bad feelings between the United States and Mexico. In the 1800s, Americans did not like Catholic religions and kings, just as they later did not like communism in the 1900s. This dislike came from old problems between England and Spain, the countries that once controlled the United States and Mexico.

During the 57 years of poor relations, the United States and Mexico had 17 different fights. Most of these fights were about land and people crossing the border to cause trouble. Both countries had to use their armies to stop bad people from attacking towns across the border.

The problems between the two countries began to get better when Mexico started to depend more on the United States. By the end of the 1800s, the United States stopped trying to take Mexican land and instead became more interested in doing business with Mexico.

Fifteen years ago, I became sick with an illness I had never heard of. It left me unable to work or care for myself.

I was a nurse then. I chose nursing because I wanted to feel safe and secure, something I did not have when I was young. People told me, "You will always find work because people will always be sick." Even though I wanted to be a scientist or news writer, I became a nurse instead.

Then at age 46, I was alone with very little money and could not work. Today, I still cannot work. After fifteen years of living on government help for sick people, I own almost nothing. I live day by day, but it is hard. I do not feel safe or good about myself. Nothing is sure anymore. But I know one thing: I could not have lived these years without help from my family and friends. When bad things happen, you do not feel strong at all.

Life will always have big and small problems. No one can be sure what will happen. Even if you get ready, some problems are too big to face alone.

I agree that in America, we should not depend only on the government. It is already weak and breaking. But I would rather see Americans learn to trust and help each other again, instead of each person trying to live alone.

Some people talk about how Americans should be strong alone. But what helped our early people live through hard times was not being alone. It was being kind, showing respect, and sharing what they had. The first people who crossed the big mountains in wagons did not make it by being alone.

So yes, be ready. I am ready. I have things for when bad times come: medical supplies, clean water items, and tape for windows. I have lights, power supplies, matches that work in rain, and food in cans. If you have land and can grow food, that is good. If you can save food for later, that is good too. Having a wood fire for heat is smart if you do not live in a big building with many homes.

But while you do all this, make friends with the people who live near you.

About 2,500 years ago, a prince was born who would later be known as Buddha. During his life, he left his wealth behind and found deep understanding. His ideas led to the start of Buddhism. Today, the oldest form of Buddhism is called Theravada Buddhism.

The religion has changed much since Buddha's time. We can see this in places like Sri Lanka, where people hold special ceremonies with water each year. Both religious teachers and common people join these events. While Buddha never spoke about such celebrations, they have become important to the people.

These changes affect both small traditions and the deep beliefs of the religion. The Buddhist community, including both teachers and followers, has had to change some of its basic ideas over time. These changes came from forces both inside and outside the religion, some friendly and some not.

To understand these changes better, we need to know some important words. Forces from inside come from Buddhist people themselves. Forces from outside come from people who are not Buddhist. Some forces try to hurt Buddhism, while others neither help nor hurt it on purpose.

At its heart, Buddhism has some basic teachings. Buddhists believe in three important things: Buddha, his teachings (called Dhamma), and the community of Buddhist teachers (called Sangha). The teachings are written in three main groups of books. These books talk about Buddha's lessons, rules for living, and deep ideas about life.

The deep ideas include beliefs like: there is no lasting soul, life includes suffering, and nothing stays the same forever. Buddhists believe that understanding these ideas can help end the cycle of being born again and again. When someone fully understands these things, they can end bad feelings like wanting too much, hating others, and being confused.

The religion has rules for living. Regular people follow five main rules: do not kill, do not lie, do not steal, do not act badly in love matters, and do not use things that change the mind. Religious teachers must follow many more rules.

The most important teaching in Buddhism involves four main truths: life includes suffering, wanting things causes suffering, suffering can end, and there is a way to end suffering.
